      answer: 'Iddah is the waiting period a woman must observe after the dissolution of her marriage before she may remarry. Its periods: (1) Divorced woman who menstruates: three complete menstrual cycles (quru) according to the majority; three tuhr (inter-menstrual intervals) according to the Shafii school. (2) Divorced woman who does not menstruate (young or post-menopausal): three lunar months. (3) Widow: four months and ten days (Quran 2:234), regardless of whether the marriage was consummated. (4) Pregnant woman: until she delivers, regardless of the above periods.',
