      question: 'What is the Hukm al-Wadi (situational ruling) as distinct from the Hukm al-Taklifi (obligational ruling)?',
      answer: 'Hukm al-Taklifi (obligational ruling) is the ruling that directly addresses the actions of accountable persons: wajib, mandub, mubah, makruh, haram. Hukm al-Wadi (situational/declaratory ruling) is a ruling that designates something as a cause (sabab), condition (shart), or impediment (mani) for another ruling, without directly commanding or prohibiting it. Examples: (1) Sabab — the entry of Ramadan is the cause (sabab) of the obligation of fasting; (2) Shart — purification (taharah) is a condition (shart) for the validity of Salah; (3) Mani — kinship within prohibited degrees is an impediment (mani) to the validity of marriage. Additional categories: Sahih/Fasid (valid/defective), Rukhsah/Azimah (concession/primary ruling). This classification was developed by the usuliyyun to give a complete account of legal relationships.',
