      answer: 'These are the three key components of Hukm al-Wadi (declaratory/situational ruling): (1) Sabab (cause) — the legal trigger: its presence brings the ruling into effect; its absence removes it. It is external and not itself commanded. Example: the entry of Ramadan (sabab) triggers the obligation of fasting. The sun\'s declining (sabab) triggers Zuhr prayer. (2) Shart (condition) — a prerequisite for the ruling\'s validity: it must be present for the ruling to take effect, but its presence alone does not trigger the ruling. Example: taharah (shart) for Salah — wudu alone does not require you to pray, but prayer is invalid without it. (3) Mani (impediment) — its presence removes a ruling or its effect despite the presence of the sabab and shart. Example: paternal relationship is a mani to marriage (you cannot marry your daughter even if all other conditions are met).',
