      answer: 'A diptote noun does not accept tanwin and takes fathah instead of kasrah in the jarr state (unless preceded by al- or in idafah, when it reverts to full declension). Causes — a noun becomes mamnu from sarf when it has TWO of the following causes, or ONE cause that counts double: (1) تَأْنِيث (femininity) — ta marbuta or alif of femininity: حَمْرَاءُ، فَاطِمَةُ; (2) عُجْمَة مَعَ العَلَمِيَّة (foreign proper noun): إِبْرَاهِيمُ، إِسْمَاعِيلُ، يُوسُفُ; (3) وَزْن الفِعْل (verb pattern) proper noun: يَزِيدُ، يَشْكُرُ; (4) الزِّيَادَة (added alif and nun): عُثْمَانُ، رَمَضَانُ، سُفْيَانُ; (5) التَّرْكِيب (compound): بَعْلَبَكُّ، حَضْرَمَوْتُ; (6) العَدْل (shifted form): عُمَرُ (from عَامِر), فُضَلُ (from فَاضِل); (7) صِيغَة مُنْتَهَى الجُمُوع (plural of abundance pattern, e.g., مَفَاعِل/مَفَاعِيل): مَسَاجِدُ، دَرَاهِمُ، أَسَاتِذَةُ — this is a single cause that counts double.',
