      answer: 'The Jumlah al-Filiyyah is a sentence beginning with a verb. Its components: (1) Al-Fil (الفِعْل — verb): can be madi, mudari, or amr; (2) Al-Fail (الفَاعِل — doer): in raf, always follows the verb; (3) Al-Maful bihi (المَفْعُول بِه — object): in nasb, for transitive verbs; (4) Additional elements: hal, tamyiz, mafuul mutlaq, mafuul fihi (zarf), etc. Default word order: Verb → Fail → Maful. Departing from this order for taqdim (fronting) creates emphasis or restriction (qasr). The verb in a verbal sentence always stays singular even if the fail is plural when the fail is explicit: ذَهَبَ الرِّجَالُ (the men went — not ذَهَبُوا when followed by explicit noun). If the fail is an implicit plural pronoun: ذَهَبُوا (they went).',
