      answer: 'Taqdim (fronting) and Takhir (delaying) refer to departing from the default word order for rhetorical and semantic purposes. Default order: Verb → Fail → Maful (verbal sentence) or Mubtada → Khabar (nominal). Departing from this order signals meaning. Types and purposes: (1) Taqdim al-Maful (fronting the object): إِيَّاكَ نَعْبُدُ (You alone we worship — iyyaka fronted before the verb, creating qasr: worship is restricted to You exclusively); (2) Taqdim al-Khabar (fronting the predicate): فِي الدَّارِ رَجُلٌ (in the house is a man — khabar fronted, making rajan the mubtada which can then be indefinite); (3) Taqdim al-Zarf (fronting the adverb): فِي الدَّارِ رَجُلٌ. Purposes of taqdim: (a) Qasr (restriction); (b) Ihtimam (speaker\'s priority — putting the most important first); (c) Preventing misunderstanding (when subject and object might be confused). Al-Jurjani in Dala\'il al-Ijaz demonstrated that the Quran always uses the most semantically precise word order.',
