      answer: 'Al-Iʿrab al-Taqdiري is when the irab vowel is present in meaning but cannot be physically shown on the word due to phonological obstacles. Types: (1) Taqdir for phonological impossibility on alif: عَصَا (staff) — in raf: عَصَاهُ is mubtada but the dammah cannot appear on the alif: يُرْفَعُ بِضَمَّةٍ مُقَدَّرَةٍ عَلَى الأَلِفِ (raised by an implied dammah on the alif); same in nasb (fathah implied) and jarr (kasrah implied). (2) Taqdir for phonological impossibility on ya following kasrah: قَاضٍ (judge) — in raf: قَاضٍ is actually قَاضِيٌ with the ya dropped for istithqal, the dammah is implied: مَرْفُوعٌ بِضَمَّةٍ مُقَدَّرَةٍ. (3) The Five Nouns in non-idafah: أَبٌ — when not in idafah, it returns to regular irab with taqdir in some analyses. (4) Damir al-mutakallim: كِتَابِي (my book) — the ya is in mahall jarr as mudaf ilayh.',
