      answer: 'The default rule: the mubtada must be a marifah (definite). An indefinite (nakirah) mubtada is only permitted when there is a specific justification (mussawwigh — لِمُسَوِّغ): (1) Preceded by negation: مَا أَحَدٌ فِي الدَّارِ (no one is in the house — the negation justifies the nakirah mubtada ahad); (2) Preceded by interrogative: هَلْ رَجُلٌ فِي الدَّارِ? (is there a man in the house?); (3) When preceded by fa of jawab al-shart: فَصَبْرٌ جَمِيلٌ (so patience is beautiful — indefinite mubtada after fa al-jawab); (4) When the khabar is a specific jar wa majrur preceding it: فِي الدَّارِ رَجُلٌ (in the house is a man — the fronted jar wa majrur justifies rajan as nakirah mubtada); (5) When the nakirah carries a meaningful specification: رَجُلٌ مِنَ العُلَمَاءِ عِنْدِي (a scholar from the scholars is with me). The Quran: وَلَعَبْدٌ مُؤْمِنٌ خَيْرٌ مِنْ مُشْرِكٍ (Quran 2:221 — the lam justifies the nakirah mubtada abd).',
