      question: 'What is the concept of الوُجُوه وَالنَّظَائِر (al-Wujuh wal-Nazair — semantic versatility) in Quranic sciences?',
      answer: 'Al-Wujuh (aspects/facets) refers to a single Quranic word that carries multiple meanings across different contexts. Al-Nazair (parallels) refers to different words that share the same meaning. This science was documented by Muqatil ibn Sulayman (d. 150 AH) in his Kitab al-Wujuh wal-Nazair. A famous example — the word قَرْء in Quran 2:228 (the iddah verse: ثَلَاثَةَ قُرُوء): it can mean menstrual period OR period of purity (tuhr) — leading directly to the well-known fiqh disagreement between the Hanafi school (menstruation) and the Shafii/Hanbali school (purity). Another example — the word يَد (hand) in Quranic usage: physical hand, power/ability (يَدُ اللَّهِ فَوْقَ أَيْدِيهِمْ — 48:10), favor/blessing (اذْكُرُوا نِعْمَتَ اللَّهِ — interpreted as blessing through yad). Understanding wujuh is essential for precise tafseer.',
