      question: 'What is the Tafseer of Surah al-Kahf and what are its major themes?',
      answer: 'Surah al-Kahf (Quran 18) is Makkan and consists of 110 verses. The Prophet ﷺ said: "Whoever memorizes ten verses from the beginning of Surah al-Kahf will be protected from the Dajjal." (Sahih Muslim 809) and recommended reciting it every Friday. Its four major narratives and their themes: (1) Ashab al-Kahf (People of the Cave) — young believers who sought refuge from a tyrannical king; theme: فِتْنَة al-Din (trial of faith in religion); (2) The Man with Two Gardens — a wealthy man who denied resurrection; theme: فِتْنَة al-Mal (trial of wealth); (3) Musa (AS) and al-Khadr — the knowledge journey; theme: فِتْنَة al-Ilm (trial of knowledge/overconfidence in one\'s understanding); (4) Dhul Qarnayn — the righteous ruler who built the barrier against Yajuj and Majuj; theme: فِتْنَة al-Sulta (trial of power). The surah is specifically linked to the Dajjal because each trial it presents is a dimension of the Dajjal\'s fitnah.',
