      id: 't28',
      question: 'What is the Tafseer of Surah Yusuf and why is it called the "best of stories" (أَحْسَنُ القَصَص)?',
      answer: 'Surah Yusuf (Quran 12) is a Makkan surah of 111 verses — the only surah dedicated entirely to one extended narrative. Allah calls it: نَحنُ نَقُصُّ عَلَيكَ أَحسَنَ القَصَصِ (We narrate to you the best of stories — 12:3). Reasons it is the best: (1) Complete narrative arc — from Yusuf\'s childhood dream to its fulfillment spanning decades; (2) Contains every human emotion: love, jealousy, betrayal, temptation, patience, gratitude, and forgiveness; (3) Comprehensive life lessons: responding to temptation (وَمَا أُبَرِّئُ نَفسِي — "I do not exonerate myself" — 12:53); patience in hardship; forgiving those who wronged you; (4) Political and administrative wisdom; (5) The theme of divine decree (qadar) — Yusuf\'s life was shaped by seemingly negative events that Allah used to establish His plan; (6) Revealed during the Year of Sadness (Am al-Huzn) to console the Prophet ﷺ. The surah ends with: لَقَد كَانَ فِي قَصَصِهِم عِبرَةٌ لِّأُولِي الأَلبَابِ (12:111 — "In their stories there is certainly a lesson for people of intelligence").',
