      question: 'What is the Tafseer of Surah al-Nur\'s verse on light (آيَة النُّور — Quran 24:35)?',
      answer: 'Quran 24:35: اللَّهُ نُورُ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالأَرضِ — "Allah is the Light of the heavens and the earth." This is one of the most discussed verses in the Quran. Tafseer approaches: (1) Literal/attributive (majority): Allah is the source and origin of all light — physical and spiritual. The heavens and earth are illuminated by His guidance, His revelation, and His management. The verse then gives an extended simile (tashbih) of divine guidance as a lamp in a niche. (2) Metaphorical (some Ashari scholars): "Allah is the Guide of the heavens and earth" — the word nur used majazically for guidance. Al-Zamakhshari in al-Kashshaf provides the most detailed rhetorical analysis of the verse\'s tashbih. Al-Ghazali wrote an entire treatise on this verse: Mishkat al-Anwar. The simile: مَثَلُ نُورِهِ كَمِشكَاةٍ فِيهَا مِصبَاحٌ — the niche (mishkah), the lamp (misbah), the glass (zujajah), the olive oil — each element symbolizing a dimension of divine guidance reaching the believer\'s heart.',
