      question: 'What is the concept of Al-Tartib al-Tawqifi (التَّرْتِيب التَّوْقِيفِي — divine ordering) of the Quran?',
      answer: 'Al-Tartib al-Tawqifi refers to the established scholarly position that the ordering of verses WITHIN each surah is divinely determined — the Prophet ﷺ directed the placement of each verse by revelation from Allah. Evidence: (1) The Prophet ﷺ would specify to the scribes where to place each new verse: "Place this verse in Surah X after verse Y." (2) The Companions scrupulously followed this order and transmitted it by mutawatir. (3) Al-Zarkashi in al-Burhan and al-Suyuti in al-Itqan extensively document the evidences for this. However: the ordering of the SURAHS relative to each other — is it divinely ordered or did the Companions determine the arrangement? Scholarly positions: (1) Majority: the surah ordering is also tawqifi (divinely directed), based on the same evidence of the Prophet\'s consistent arrangement in recitation; (2) Minority: the surah ordering was determined by the Companions\' ijtihad based on considerations of length and frequency of revelation; (3) Hybrid position (al-Suyuti): some surahs are tawqifi in their ordering; others were determined by the Companions.',
