      question: 'What is the Al-Tafseer al-Mawduii (التَّفْسِير المَوْضُوعِي — thematic tafseer) and how does it differ from classical tafseer?',
      answer: 'Al-Tafseer al-Mawduii (thematic/topical tafseer) is a modern methodological approach that studies a single topic across all Quranic references to it, gathering all relevant verses and synthesizing a comprehensive Quranic perspective. It differs from classical sequential tafseer (tahlili) which proceeds verse-by-verse through the entire Quran. Types: (1) Thematic study of a surah — analyzing the internal unity and main themes of a single surah; (2) Thematic study across the entire Quran — gathering all verses on a single concept (e.g., justice, the human soul, the role of prophets). Pioneer scholars: Muhammad al-Ghazali\'s thematic reading of surahs; Bint al-Shati\'s (Aisha Abd al-Rahman) literary approach; Abd al-Sattar Fath Allah Said\'s Al-Madkhal ila al-Tafseer al-Mawduii. Advantages: reveals the Quran\'s comprehensive treatment of major themes; disadvantages: risk of importing pre-formed conclusions into the analysis rather than deriving them from the text.',
